<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06258012 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06258012 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  HAYWARD; MAN; BANK; ROBBERY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A Hayward bank robber dropped his wig, beard, trench coat and the money hestole while making a hasty getaway Friday, police said.;   Shortly afterward,Hayward police arrested Andrew Vincent Nunez, 34, of San Jose on suspicion ofbank robbery.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  HOLDUP SUSPECT DROPS HIS PROPS, IS ARRESTED  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     About 1:30 p.m., neighbors called police after noticing a suspiciouslooking man outside the California Federal Bank, 24299 Southland Drive. Theman then dressed in a wig, beard and trench coat entered the bank, acted asthough he had a weapon and demanded money, police said.;   While the man wasrunning from the bank, he dropped his disguise and the money.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910914  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  September  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  101  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday, September 14, 199100258012,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>